<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 56 Feared Dead in North Indian Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 56 people are feared
dead and property worth millions of rupees destroyed in Kinnaur
and Shimla in north India's Himachal Pradesh following flash
floods in Sutluj river Monday night, officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
About 20 persons are missing in Kinnaur district and Rampur in
Shimla, they said.
</P>
<P>
Himachal Chief Minister Prem Kumar Dhumal, who visited the
affected areas of Kinnaur district said that the flooded river was
flowing about 25 feet above normal level at many points.
</P>
<P>
He said all links in Kinnaur were cut off as about 30
kilometers of National Highway 22 and 14 bridges were washed away
in Kinnaur while the Wangto bridge was hanging useless. The death
toll was feared to go up, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, the state government had
set up a control room at the state headquarters which would be in
touch with the administration of the affected districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
