<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Militants Kill Eight Pilgrims in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- In the first major attack on
pilgrims, militants on Tuesday shot dead eight people and injured
20 others at a pilgrim camp in Pahalgam in west Kashmir, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
Militants fired indiscriminately on the pilgrims at the camp at
around 6 p.m. Tuesday, killing eight of them on the spot, the PTI
quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, militants attacked a pilgrim camp in Jammu
region with grenades and indiscriminate firing, but no pilgrim or
civilian was injured in that attack, the PTI added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
