<HEADLINE> Iranian Speaker Hails Lebanese Resistance Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (parliament) speaker
Mehdi Karrubi here on Wednesday hailed the Lebanese resistance
movement against Israel, saying it created great epics during the
past two decades.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with his Lebanese counterpart Nabih Berri, Karrubi
congratulated the Lebanese nation and government on the Israeli
withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli pullout on May 24, after more than 20 years of
occupation, was a great victory of the unbreakable Lebanese
resistance movement and the unity showed between the Lebanese
people and their government, Karrubi said, quoted by the official
IRNA news agency.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced Iran's readiness to help Lebanon's
reconstruction, which is a difficult task because of the lengthy
war against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Berri, who arrived here Wednesday for an official visit, thanked
Iran for its long-time support and assistance to the Lebanese
resistance movement.
</P>
<P>
Calling the Israeli withdrawal as the first big victory for
Arabs and Muslims, he urged Muslim countries to strengthen
solidarity in order to safeguard this great triumph.
</P>
<P>
Both officials expressed satisfaction with their bilateral
relations. They also called for more efforts to enhance
cooperation, especially between the two parliaments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
