<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Captures 30 "Caribbean Cartel" Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombian police has captured 30
persons, allegedly members of the "Caribbean Cartel," in the
north of the country, reported Wednesday the local radio network
RCN.
</P>
<P>
The source said that the "Ground-swell" operation, commanded by
National Police director General Luis Ernesto Gilibert Vargas, was
the second most important against drug trafficking, after the "
Millennium" operation.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-one crackdowns were practiced in Barranquilla, four in
Monteria, one in Cartagena, one in Santa Maria, and three in the
city of Ocana, in the Norte de Santander department.
</P>
<P>
One of the persons detained is Libardo Parra, considered by the
authorities as the head of the criminal organization, who used to
send cocaine and heroin to the United States and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The Attorney General Office, the General Prosecutorship of the
Nation and the United States Drug Enforcement Administration took
part in the operation, together with the police.
</P>
<P>
The 30 detained persons were taken to Bogota, where they will
be presented to the press at the Police general direction.
</P>
</TEXT>
