<HEADLINE> Uzbek President Appoints Key Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Uzbek President Islam Karimov
appointed three key ministers Wednesday in the latest cabinet
reshuffle, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Rustam Azimov was named deputy prime minister in charge of
economic affairs, Interfax said, quoting the presidential
administration.
</P>
<P>
Azimov, previously a chairman of the National Foreign Economic
Affairs Bank, will keep his portfolio as finance minister.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Agriculture and Water Resources Minister Turop
Kholtayev was promoted to the post of deputy prime minister in
charge of agriculture and related industries.
</P>
<P>
The third appointment was of Rustam Shoabdurakhmanov, who was
named minister of macroeconomics and statistics. Shoabdura khmanov,
previously first deputy minister of macroeconomics and statistics,
had worked on the presidential administration. 
