<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's Zyuganov Warns of Political Crisis in Autumn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian Communist leader Gennady
Zyuganov warned Wednesday that the country will face a political
crisis in the autumn, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Contrary to the declarations of the current authorities about a
strong state, Zyuganov said, Russia is increasingly moving toward
a right-wing liberal, pro-American economy.
</P>
<P>
"We see that a stubborn covert struggle is underway at the top,
which may develop into strong confrontation in autumn," Interfax
quoted Zyuganov as saying at a meeting with editors of several
regional left-wing opposition publications.
</P>
<P>
"A contradictory situation is evolving in the country. On the
one hand, the authorities proclaim ideas that we have advocated
for 10 years and have won support from the overwhelming majority
of the population. On the other, a right-wing liberal,pro-American
line is evolving in the economy and an offensive is underway
against the social rights of working people, which aggravates
social tension," Zyuganov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
