<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Urges Support for Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi on Wednesday called on Muslim countries to back
Palestinians in their struggle for an independent state, the
official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have the right to establish an independent
state with Jerusalem as its capital, Kharrazi told his Saudi,
Malaysian and Senegalese counterparts on separate phone calls, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
During the telephone conversations, Kharrazi underlined the need
to mobilize support among Islamic countries for the legitimate
rights of Palestinians. He reiterated Iran's stance that Jerusalem
should be the eternal capital of Palestine and all Palestinian
refugees should be allowed to return home.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi termed the current situation in the Middle East as
sensitive, as the Palestinians and Israel have just ended their
Camp David peace talks without achieving any agreement. The 15-day
marathon talks mediated by the United States ended in failure due
to wide gaps over the fate of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi also urged the Organization of the Islamic Conference,
currently chaired by Iran, to adopt appropriate measures on the
Middle East issue at this sensitive juncture.
</P>
<P>
In response, the foreign ministers of Saudi Arabia, Malaysia and
Senegal also stressed the need for Islamic solidarity in support of
Palestine and welcomed Iran's initiative in this respect, IRNA
said.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Kharrazi held separate phone talks with the foreign
ministers of Syria, Egypt, Qatar and Jordan to coordinate their
stands.
</P>
<P>
Iran refuses to recognize Israel and has opposed any peace talks
and agreements with the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
It has always called for armed struggle against Israeli
occupation of Arab and Islamic lands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
