<HEADLINE> Central African Students Occupy Embassy For 5th Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Students from the Central African
Republic continued their occupation of their embassy in Moscow for
the fifth day Wednesday, demanding the payment of overdue stipends.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the action said they have not received stipends
for 18 months and they were forced to get obtain money from
relatives or borrowing from students from other countries, the
Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
There are some 25 people in the embassy, which occupies two
apartments in an apartment block in southwest Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The students say they do not have any contacts with the
ambassador because "he has nothing to do with it." Instead, they
telephoned their education minister who allegedly promised to pay
at least part of the money "today or tomorrow, but in any case
this week."
</P>
<P>
The students, who started the occupation last Saturday, have
refused to disclose the size of their stipends or the total sum of
the arrears, Interfax said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
