<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Venture Capital Investment Still Hot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A report released Wednesday
said that the effect of April's public market shake-out in the
United States on venture capital-backed company valuations as a
whole was relatively insignificant.
</P>
<P>
Venture-backed companies raised 17.2 billion U.S. dollars in 1,
054 rounds of financing in the second quarter this year, according
to the report from San Francisco-based venture capital research
firm VentureOne.
</P>
<P>
Although both deal flow and the amount invested decreased
mildly this quarter, by 3 percent and 6 percent, respectively-
overall venture investment for the first half of the year is close
to the total for all of 1999, and Internet-specific investment has
already exceeded last year's total, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Information technology (IT) companies had their strongest
quarter ever. Investment in this industry group rose 10 percent
from last quarter, to 10 billion dollars. Every segment within IT
saw an increase in activity, with communications, information
services and software setting particularly impressive records.
Venture capital investment in IT now stands at more than twice the
level it had attained at this time last year.
</P>
<P>
Venture-backed companies raised a record of 17.8 billion
dollars in 1,040 rounds of financing in the first quarter,
according to VentureOne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
