<HEADLINE> Passenger Jeep Falls Into River in Manila, 18 Feared Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 18 people were feared
dead after a passenger jeepney fell from a flooded bridge in
Quezon city, Metro Manila on Wednesday night, a TV report said.
</P>
<P>
The country's biggest network ABS-CBN quoted initial reports as
saying that most of those reported still missing were women and
children who were trapped inside the passenger jeepney which lost
control after being washed away by the overflowing Marikina river.
</P>
<P>
Two of its passengers, including a woman, were later retrieved
by responding rescue workers after they were able to swim for
safety, the ABS-CBN noted.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said the driver of the 20-seater passenger
jeepney was trying to ride through the Tumana bridge but was swept
away by the rushing floodwaters overflowing on the bridge.
