<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, August 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy resigned on
Wednesday from the government led by Prime Minister Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement at his office inside the Knesset (parliament)
, Levy said he has submitted his resignation letter to Barak
Wednesday morning, in which he detailed his reasons for
resignation.
</P>
<P>
"I can not accept Prime Minister Barak's peace policies
concerning the negotiations with the Palestinians, because Barak
had made too many concessions to the Palestinians at the Camp
David summit, particularly on the Jerusalem issue," Levy said. (
Israel-FM-Resignation)
</P>
