CAIRO -- The Palestinians on Wednesday called for full
implementation of the United Nations Security Council resolutions
in a bid to end the half-century-long Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
The only way to peace in the Middle East is the "honest
implementation of the U.N. Security Council resolutions 242 and
338," Palestinian Ambassador to Egypt Zohdi al Qedra said after a
meeting between Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat in Alexandria. (Egypt-Palestine-UN
Resolutions)
</P>
