- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A ranking Russian general said Wednesday that the
country's federal troops have killed nearly 14,000 Chechen rebels
in the past year, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The announcement by Deputy Chief of the General Staff General
Valery Manilov coincided with the one-year anniversary of the
start of anti-terrorist operations in the North Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
The military campaign was launched after two waves of armed
Chechen incursions into neighboring Dagestan and a series of
apartment building explosions that left over 300 people dead in
Moscow and two other cities. (Russia-Chechnya-Rebels)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Ninety-eight people have been killed in flash
floods in north India's Himachal Pradesh state since Monday night,
the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the victims, 53 were from the worst-hit Kinnaur district
alone, while districts of Shimla and Mandi also reported heavy
casualties, the PTI quoted local authorities as saying. (India-
Flood-Death) 
