<HEADLINE> Man. United Leads Financial Turnover in European Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- English Premiership club Manchester
United take the lead in annual turnover in European football,
according to local report on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
L'Equipe sports daily listed United's annual turnover at 132
million dollars, followed by Bayern Munich (124 million) and
European Champions League winners Real Madrid (107 million).
</P>
<P>
The report also published a list of the 20 biggest-spending
clubs ahead of the new season. Italian champion Lazio led with 99
million dollars, followed by Parma (90 million) and Real Madrid (
84 million). 
</P>
