<HEADLINE> Kobe To Build "New Chinese Street" In Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Sasayama Kazutoshi, mayor of Kobe,
held a press conference today in Tianjin, to encourage
entrepreneurs in Asian countries to expand businesses in its "New
Chinese Street."
</P>
<P>
Sasayama said the street is located on a man-made island in
Kobe, occupying an area of 390 sq.m. The street will be a business
center with Chinese enterprises and Japanese firms dealing in
businesses with China, involving tourism, Chinese-languages
software and advertising.
</P>
<P>
"New Chinese Street" will provide trade-related services such
as legal services, accounting, consultation, patent applications
and economic and trade negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The city will also build the street into a distribution center
and a training center.
</P>
<P>
The construction is part of Kobe's efforts to intensify
cultural exchanges between the two countries, said the mayor,
adding that enterprises which set up their agencies in the street
before March 2002 will be granted subsidized land.
</P>
<P>
Chinese cultural centers, libraries, bookstores, societies for
Chinese and Japanese cultural exchanges, and entertaining centers
will be built in the street as well.  
</P>
</TEXT>
