<HEADLINE> Chinese Customs Catch Nine Stowaways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Customs at the airport of Fuzhou
city in east China's Fujian province arrested nine stowaways in
July.
</P>
<P>
The nine persons, including two children, were arrested on July
11 and 28.
</P>
<P>
Five of them had fake permanent residence certificates from the
United States. They would pay 55,000 US dollars each to "
snakeheads" if they succeeded in getting to the U.S.
</P>
<P>
The remaining four persons held fake U.S. visas and agreed to
pay "snakehead" 53,000 US dollars each after arriving in the U.S.
</P>
