<HEADLINE> Fire at Immigration Tower Injures 47 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A fire broke out inside a unit
on the 13th floor of the Immigration Tower of Hong Kong around 06:
00 p.m. Wednesday, causing 47 injured, including 23 staff members
of the Immigration Department of Hong Kong, according to a
government spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The injured, at least three of whom were in serious condition,
were rushed to hospitals for treatment, and the fire was
extinguished by actuation of sprinkler head prior to firemen's
arrival, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive of Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Tung Chee Hwa went to one of the hospitals and visited the victims
soon after he was informed of the incident.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that at the time of incident, inflammable
liquid was splashed and lit inside the unit, which led to an
explosion. The case was still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
