<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Injured Philippine Ambassador Said to Be Out of Danger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Ambassador to Indonesia
Leonides Caday, who was injured in a powerful bomb explosion in
Jakarta Tuesday, has been declared out of danger by doctors at a
private hospital there, the Philippine government said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Caday underwent a successful operation at midnight Tuesday on
the multiple fractures and wounds he sustained in the explosion,
the Department of Foreign Affairs (DFA) said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Joseph Estrada, who is on the last leg of
a 10-day working visit in the United States, in a press statement
said that he strongly condemned this barbaric act and expressed
the resolve to "fight terrorism in all forms wherever it might
take place."
</P>
<P>
"Once again the ugly head of terrorist forces has taken the
lives and injured hardworking diplomatic representatives of the
Philippines, "the president said.
</P>
<P>
He said formal reports from the Indonesian government are being
awaited from intelligence services as to who is responsible for
the despicable act.
</P>
<P>
He added: "I fully commiserate with the families of the
deceased and we are thankful to God that the life of Ambassador
Leonides Caday, one of our most senior and efficient diplomats,
has been spared."
</P>
<P>
The doctors of Caday performed on him a three-hour operation
where metal pins were inserted to connect the five leg fractures
he sustained, the DFA said.
</P>
<P>
The DFA also said Caday suffered bruises in his head, hands and
upper body, as well as burns in his hand and hair, adding the
ambassador was conscious all throughout the operation as only
local anesthesia was applied.
</P>
<P>
The governor of Jakarta as well as top military and police
officials visited Caday Tuesday night to extend all the support
and assistance that may be required, the DFA said.
</P>
<P>
Acting Assistant Secretary for Personnel Reynaldo Catapang has
been instructed to fly to Jakarta immediately to assist Caday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
