<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Kashmir Massacres Up to 100 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of victims in a
series of militant attacks in Kashmir since Tuesday night has
risen to 100, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported on Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims are Hindus, said the PTI, adding that
scores of others were wounded in the attacks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the death toll in the first and the largest massacre
on Tuesday evening at Pahalgam town in west Kashmir, where
militants fired indiscriminately at the crowd in a pilgrim camp,
had surged to 35 from the earlier reported 32 as more wounded
people succumbed to injuries in the hospital, the PTI noted.
</P>
<P>
Among the 35 were 23 pilgrims and eight Muslims, mainly
shopkeepers and porters, it added.
</P>
<P>
In the latest development, Indian Home Affairs Minister L K
Advani was quoted by the PTI as saying that Pakistan-based
militant outfit Lashkar-e-Toiba was behind the killings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
