<HEADLINE> Death Toll in North India Floods Rises to 98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Ninety-eight people have been
killed in flash floods in north India's Himachal Pradesh state
since Monday night, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the victims, 53 were from the worst-hit Kinnaur district
alone, while districts of Shimla and Mandi also reported heavy
casualties, the PTI quoted local authorities as saying.
</P>
<P>
As the floods cut off power supply and road links in many areas,
the exact number of deaths from other affected regions was not yet
available and the death toll was likely to go up, a local official
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Himachal state government has asked the central government
for a financial assistance of 5 billion rupees (about 110 million
U.S. dollars) for flood relief, an earlier PTI report said on
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
