<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania: Peak Exports in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Romania's exports rose to 926.1
million U.S. dollars in June, a record high since 1989, the local
press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The result was 16.9 percent more than last May, and 27.2
percent more than June 1999, the official Rompres news agency
quoted the state statistics office as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, imports climbed to 1.17 billion dollars, an increase
of 4.1 percent over the previous month and 28.8 percent over the
figure a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, the east European country's
exports reached 4.91 billion dollars, 27.4 percent up from the
same period in 1999; while imports rose sharply to 5.84 billion
dollars, an increase of 19.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
June's trade deficit was 247.7 million dollars compared to 182.
9 million dollars in June 1999. For the first six months of this
year, the deficit was 934.3 million dollars, compared with 1.02
billion dollars a year before.
</P>
<P>
For Romania, Italy proved to be its largest trading partner,
which ranked first in terms of both export and import. The other
important exporters of Romanian products were Germany, Turkey,
France and Britain.
</P>
<P>
In terms of exports to Romania, Italy was followed by Germany,
Russia, France and Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
