<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian General Says 14,000 Chechen Rebels Eliminated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A ranking Russian general said
Wednesday that the country's federal troops have killed nearly 14,
000 Chechen rebels in the past year, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The announcement by Deputy Chief of the General Staff General
Valery Manilov coincided with the one-year anniversary of the
start of anti-terrorist operations in the North Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
The military campaign was launched after two waves of armed
Chechen incursions into neighboring Dagestan and a series of
apartment building explosions that left over 300 people dead in
Moscow and two other cities.
</P>
<P>
Manilov said the federal units were confronted by "a well-
manned, armed, equipped and trained terrorist army of about 26,000
men, of whom over 5,000 were mercenaries."
</P>
<P>
At the start of the operation, the rebels had nearly 30 tanks,
over 60 combat vehicles and armored personnel carriers, 15 self-
propelled anti-aircraft systems, a battery of multiple rocket
launchers, and over 20 pieces of large caliber artillery and
mortars, according to the general.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of the rebel forces have been defeated, but small
rebel groups totaling nearly 2,000 men, about 500 of them
mercenaries, are continuing to fight against the federal units, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
