<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Czech Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Three Polish nationals were killed
and seven others injured when two vehicles collided head-on along
the road from Hranice to Lipnik nad Becvou in South Moravia this
morning, the Czech News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 4 a.m., when a car licensed in
Poland drifted into the opposite lane and smashed into an oncoming
vehicle. Two people died on the spot, another died after transfer
to hospital. A four-year-old child was among the dead.
</P>
