<HEADLINE> Heart-Lung Transplant Recipient Lives Over 100 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese farmer has lived for
more than 100 days with a transplanted heart and lungs.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wenbin, a 31-year old man from the city of Yongkang in
east China's Zhejiang Province, was born with a life-threatening
heart condition.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990s, Zhang's heart condition took a turn for the worse
and he was diagnosed as having pulmonary hypertension, a disease
hard to cure.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was admitted into the No. 1 Hospital attached to Zhejiang
University in Hangzhou, the provincial capital, in November 1999.
</P>
<P>
He underwent a joint transplant operation on April 16 this year,
receiving a donated heart and lungs.
</P>
<P>
The surgery proved successful. Zhang's transplanted heart and
lungs are reportedly in good order.  
</P>
</TEXT>
