<HEADLINE> China Develops Key Part of Nuclear Power Reactor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- China announced today that it
has developed the core part of a nuclear power reactor that has a
generating capacity of one million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
The core part is made for the nuclear power station in Ling'ao
in south China's Guangdong province. This is the second large-
scale commercial nuclear station that the province built after the
completion of the Daya Bay nuclear station.
</P>
<P>
The 127-ton core part of the nuclear reactor is developed by
Shanghai No.1 Tool Works in cooperation with Framatone Group from
France.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai company took three years to develop and make the
core part, laying a sound foundation for localizing the technology
of producing nuclear reactors in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
