<HEADLINE> Beijing Ancient Tomb Looted A Long Time Ago </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists said that the Han
Dynasty (206 BCE-220 AD) tomb under excavation in western suburbs
of Beijing may have been looted a long time ago as they found
today two tunnels dug by looters on the outer walls of the tomb.
</P>
<P>
However, the looters might have stolen only a few small-sized
relics from the tomb because both tunnels are wide enough for only
one person to squeeze through, said archeologists. They believe
that they will make some amazing discoveries when they open the
tomb's inner chamber.
</P>
<P>
The tomb was found as police seized several people who tried to
loot the tomb earlier this year. It is the second largest tomb of
the Han Dynasty found in Beijing, following the Dabaotai tomb in
southwestern suburbs of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
