<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Cools Hot Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The first heavy rain to hit
Beijing, the Chinese capital, this summer, with some tiny hail,
poured down in Beijing this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A warm and humid air current met with a cold air current,
producing the heavy rain accompanied by thunder, said
meteorologists.
</P>
<P>
The rain was a great relief to the overheated city. It fell
during rush hour causing traffic problems.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the rain will last till late in the night.
</P>
