<HEADLINE> Iranian Army Kills MKO Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- At least five members of the Iraq-
based Mujaheddin Khalq Organization (MKO) were killed by Iran's
army when they tried to infiltrate into the Iranian territory, the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The "terrorist" MKO members who were intending to infiltrate
into the Iranian territory were killed during a cross-border
conflict with the army units stationed in the border region of
Dehloran, an army statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement further added the MKO fired several mortars
from across the border, which resulted in the death of two Iranian
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In the operations, a number of weapons and ammunition were also
confiscated by the army personnel.
</P>
<P>
The MKO, a major political and military group which had fought
against the Iranian Shah regime before the 1979 Islamic revolution,
was outlawed in 1981 and fled into Iraq following sharp differences
with the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
Labeled by Iran as a "terrorist group," the MKO has launched
numerous cross-border attacks inside Iran in recent years,
including assassinating senior Iranian officials. 
</P>
