<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Inter-Korean trade amounted to 202.
8 million U.S. dollars in the first half of this year, up 22.9
percent from the same period in 1999, the Unification Ministry
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Exports from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
to South Korea hit 64.49 million U.S. dollars in the first six-
month period, up 41.6 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports from South Korea to the DPRK reached 138.3 million
dollars, up 15.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK mainly exported agricultural, forestry and maritime
goods to the south, while South Korea's exports included home
appliances such as color TV sets.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the amount of "processing-on-commission" trade
between the two countries has also risen greatly, according to the
ministry. 
