<HEADLINE> Killed Policeman Becomes A Martyr </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Municipal Government today
granted a title of revolutionary martyr to police officer Yuan
Shiguang, who was killed by two armed men on July 23.
</P>
<P>
Two businessmen Zhang Lin and He Qi, who were wounded helping
Yuan, also commended and given 5,000 yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Yuan, 34, with the Haidian Branch of Beijing Public Security
Bureau, was at the Summer Palace when he noticed two young men
acting suspiciously among the large crowd of visitors on July 23.
</P>
<P>
The two men drew a knife and stabbed Yuan in the stomach.
Zhang and He Qi, who are not from Beijing, came up to help Yuan.
The man who stabbed Yuan also knifed the two businessmen, one in
the arm and the other in the chest.
</P>
<P>
Despite their injuries, Yuan, Zhang and He ran after the
fleeing suspects. Yuan ran for about 70 meters before he fell to
the ground and died.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and He chased after one of the suspects for about a
kilometer and caught him.
</P>
<P>
The second suspect was caught in western Beijing five hours
after.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the past 20 years show that more than 5,000
Chinese police have died in the line of duty and 100,000 more were
injured. Some 533 policemen lost their lives and 5,885 were
wounded last year while on the job.  
</P>
</TEXT>
