<HEADLINE> 10 Farmers Choked to Death in Northeastern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Ten young farmers in Iran's
northeastern Khorasan Province were choked to death on Tuesday when
they descended a well and tried to deepen it, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Two of the victims descended the well, in a small village of 40
households, in order to deepen it for water, but they were poisoned
to death by gas, a local government official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The eight others, who were waiting for their friends to re-
emerge, were also poisoned by the gas when they tried to descend
the well, he added.
</P>
<P>
Due to a widespread drought that has severely hit Iran, the
well, which the whole village depends on, was on the verge of
drying up and had gathered gas, said the official.
</P>
<P>
Iran is suffering from a particularly dry summer this year that
has worsened the drought problem, which the country has been facing
since last year.
</P>
<P>
Drought has hit most parts of the country, inflicting heavy
damages. In some areas, riots even broke out due to the lack of
potable water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
