<HEADLINE> Violence Continues in Maluku, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Violence continued in Indonesia's
Maluku province, claiming 23 lives and injuring two others.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency, three people were injured
as bombs and grenades exploded in Ambon, capital of Maluku, on
Wednesday noon.
</P>
<P>
Security officers blocked the roads to the site of the
explosions as students left their schools.
</P>
<P>
Another major violence rocked Maluku on Tuesday, claiming 23
lives and injuring two others.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a group of people attacked Waal village,
Salahutu subdistrict in central Maluku. The attack led to the
postponement of a dialogue among religious leaders in Ambon.
</P>
<P>
The spice islands of Maluku have been wrecked by communal
clashes between Christians and Muslims since early 1999. Thousands
of people were either killed or wounded and thousands of houses
and dozens of houses of worship destroyed. 
</P>
