<HEADLINE> Czech Air Force Pilot Dies in Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 2, (Xinhua) -- A Czech Air Force pilot was
killed in a plane crash Tuesday afternoon at Chrudim, a central
area of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
According to the Czech newspaper "Lidove Noviny," the L-29
training plane crashed in a corn field Tuesday while returning to
its base after completing its daily flight plan. No one on the
ground was injured.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash is not clear, but an Investigation is
under way.
</P>
<P>
This is the second crash of a Czech military plane in six weeks.
On June 16, a Czech Air Force SU-22 fighter crashed in the central
Trebic area. That pilot also perished in the accident.
</P>
<P>
A total of 25 aviation accidents have occurred in the Czech
Republic during the past 10 years, resulting in the deaths of 21
pilots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
