<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Food Expo 2000, a summer
gourmet affair for food lovers, will be held from August 17 to 21
at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC), the
fair will have two exhibition halls for a variety of food products,
taking up over 11,000 square meters of exhibition area.
</P>
<P>
Some 215 food manufacturers and distributors from the Chinese
mainland, Hong Kong, Taiwan and the Republic of Korea will be
present at the Expo that will be categorized into nine zones
including beverages, bakery products and health food.
</P>
<P>
At a preview for the Food Expo Wednesday, Anne Chick, senior
exhibitions manager of TDC, said the fair is a large-scale food
and beverages promotion event for the public, and it will help
stimulate further growth of local food industry.  
