<HEADLINE> HK Ocean Park Launches Summer Promotion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Ocean Park has
launched during the summer vacation a series of promotion
activities to attract more visitors.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the promotion activities is a lucky draw.
Every guest visiting Ocean Park will get a scratch win game card
and the prizes include a family sedan car, overseas trips, audio
visual appliances, and other charming things.
</P>
<P>
More new clowns and amusements have been imported from overseas
for this summer, mainly from Europe and the United States, to make
the park more entertaining to visitors.
</P>
<P>
Visitors wandering around the park are very likely to meet with
the 2.5-meter-tall giant coming newly from France or bump into two
eccentric fighters who will spray water on you with water guns.
</P>
<P>
Exotic Brazilian dances, Chinese acrobatics, and even the
unique feat of the Sichuan Opera, Bianlian (change of faces), are
presented at one corner of the park, giving visitors a refreshing
experience of a mix of different cultures.
</P>
<P>
"Ocean Park is ranked among the top 25 ocean parks in the world,
" said Paul Pei, director of sales and marketing of the park. He
promised to bring new experience to visitors with the launch of
colorful new activities.
</P>
<P>
Ocean Park is one of the most popular attractions in Hong Kong,
drawing some 3 million visitors a year, and 40 percent of them
come from outside Hong Kong, mainly from inland areas of China.
</P>
</TEXT>
