<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ended 8.16 points lower
to close at 2,065.92 points in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 435.39 million units worth
532.78 million Singapore dollars (307.97 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 172 to 145 with 243 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
StraTech was the most active stock with a turnover of 74.27
million units. It was followed by IPCO which had 23.84 million
shares done. SMRT was the next with 23.22 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
PacCent led gainers of the day rising by 80 cents to close at
25.20 Singapore dollars. GreatEast picked up 45 cents to finish at
6.35 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem moved up 40 cents to end at 14.
10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture headed the descent of the day incurring a loss of 90
cents to close at 19.70 Singapore dollars. SPH and SPH 100 sank 80
cents to finish at 28.70 and 28.50 Singapore dollars respectively.
Chartered shed 60 cents to end at 12.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that stocks ended slightly lower in quiet trading
as investors searched for fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
They said that gains in financial stocks were offset by losses
in electronics counters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
