<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Surge 2.25 Percent As Interest Rate Fears Ease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index, after a plain opening, shoot up
286.26 points to finish the morning session at 17,183.71. In the
following trading, the index climbed up further, to close the day'
s trading 379.94 points, or 2.25 percent higher, at 17,277.39.
</P>
<P>
However, Tech stocks suffered selling pressure after the Nasdaq
composite index continued its downtrend amid earnings fears.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 14.569 billion HK dollars (about 1.868
billion U.S. dollars), smaller than Tuesday's 15.322 billion HK
dollars (about 1.964 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The four sub-indexes of the HSI reaped across-the-board gains,
with Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry rising
by 2.47 percent, 1.27 percent, 1.71 percent and 2.34 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
But Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index suffered losses, going down by 1.49 percent
and 1.30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng IT Index and Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index gained 2.76
percent and 0.23 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
