<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore, Israeli Firms Launch Joint Technology Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singapore Exchange-listed Keppel Telecommunications &AMP;
Transportation (Keppel T&AMP;T) and Israel's leading financial
investment group Shrem Fudim Kelner Group (SFK) announced the set-
up of their 50-50 joint venture capital partnership.
</P>
<P>
The two partners, together with their strategic investors, will
commit the fund to investing in and supporting the development of
companies in high-growth technology, media and telecoms sectors.
</P>
<P>
Most of these investments will be targeted in Israel, the
United States, and Europe markets, directed towards private
equities companies requiring expansion and mid-stage funding.
</P>
<P>
Aside from capital funding, the joint venture company will also
offer strategy consultation and professional support services such
as operational advice to the firms it invests in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
