<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Combats Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A severe drought affecting one-
third of crops in east China's Jiangxi Province, a major grain
producer, has eased thanks to two weeks of cloud seeding efforts.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said the cloud seeding operations have brought
rainfall to more than 66,600 ha of crops in 66 counties and cities.
</P>
<P>
In neighboring Anhui Province, farmers are fighting the worst
drought in 50 years. About 400,000 pumps are being used and
millions of dollars spent for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
The drought began to affect Anhui in the winter of 1999, and
the northern part of the province has had only half as much
rainfall as in normal years.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 853,000 ha of farmland has been affected,
and 638,000 people have had difficulty getting drinking water.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that dry weather will linger for about two more
weeks in the two provinces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
