<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasuries extended the
rise today, led by the three bonds listed after 1999, as the
capital locked in last Friday's stock subscriptions was released
and flowed into the market.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 2.57 billion yuan, swelling by 839 million
yuan as compared with that of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009908 (3.30 percent, due 2009) jumped the most to 102.50
yuan, 0.32 percent higher than the last close price. The bond met
with a strong demand and accomplished a trade value of 1.08
billion yuan. The other bond listed in 1999, the eight-year 009905,
rose by 0.27 percent to 102.72 yuan to follow the top gainer.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year floating-rate 010004, with the annual coupon rate
at 2.87 percent this year, climbed 0.26 percent to the historical
high of 103.25 yuan, sending the yield down by 0.03 percent to 2.
52 percent. The trade also expanded more than four folds to 289
million yuan, helped by the revival of the overall T-bond market.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market stayed quiet with the combined turnover of
three-day, 14-day and 28-day repo transactions up 439 million yuan
to 2.37 billion yuan. The close price of the tree-day transaction
closed unchanged at 3.18 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
