<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Up Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- China's fund market continued to
move upwards Wednesday, according to Homeway, a leading online
financial information provider.
</P>
<P>
Among the 28 funds on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets,
26 rose and two remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Stock Exchange Fund Index, which represents the 13
funds on the Shanghai market, continued to keep a rising trend,
consecutively creating new highs. Today, it broke through 1,100
points, and once reached 1,105.74 points. It finally closed at 1,
095.93 points, up 1.45 percent compared with 1,080.27 points of
last close.
</P>
<P>
The turnover also expanded. The turnover of the 13 funds
amounted to 1.483 billion fund units, increasing 22.56 percent
compared with Tuesday's 1.211 billion fund units, implying that
loose money continued to flow into the market.
</P>
<P>
The top gainer today was the restructured Fund Tongzhi. Among
the 22 funds that were in discounted trading, Fund Tongsheng had
the biggest rise, up 2.75 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
