<HEADLINE> Rivaldo Will Stay With Barcelona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona have managed to hold on
World Player Rivaldo at the club for the next three years by
raising his salary to more than $5.6 million per year.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo had talks with Barcelona president Joan Gaspart until
late on Tuesday before reaching an agreement that some reports
estimated will more than double Rivaldo's salary and make him the
highest-paid soccer player in the world.
</P>
<P>
Neither the club nor Rivaldo would reveal the exact number, but
the Brazilian midfieler's new after-tax salary will be more than a
billion pesetas ($5.6 million per year), according to reports by
Spanish media.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona had rejected a transfer offer from AC Milan last
month.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo is going to join the team on Wednesday at the preseason
training camp in Hoenderloo, the Netherlands. 
</P>
