<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China's Steel Giant Makes More Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Anshan Iron and Steel Company (
Group), a steel giant which has long been mired in difficulty,
scored 160 million yuan of profit (19.3 million U.S. dollars) in
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Angang, as the northeast China-based steel giant is also known,
has met the goal for the whole year ahead of schedule. Its profit
in the January-June period is twice as much as its annual profit
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe the achievement indicates that this steel giant
is now revitalizing.
</P>
<P>
Angang increased its output of iron, steel, billets and rolled
steel in the first half of this year, and its total output was
within the quotas set by the State. It earned 122 million U.S.
dollars from exports,a rise of seven times from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it has shifted to exporting more steel sheets from
selling primary steel products.
</P>
<P>
Angang currently is the biggest producer of cold-rolled steel
products in China, with an annual output of over two million tons.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province to Attract More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
selected 115 projects to open to overseas investment, and a
promotional campaign will be launched in Shenzhen later this month.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's vice governor Zhang Ping said these projects cover such
areas as infrastructure, agriculture and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
More preferential policies, including tax breaks and easy loans,
will be made available to attract investors, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Anhui approved the establishment of 83 overseas-funded
enterprises during the first five months of the year, with
combined contractual overseas capital of 76.52 million U.S.
dollars, a rise of 172 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises are related with infrastructure, agriculture,
information technology, and machinery.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Anhui Provincial Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Commission attributed the high growth to an
improved business environment in the province.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has already issued a series of new policies to attract
overseas business people since the beginning of last year, and
they include measures to protect the legitimate rights and
interests of overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Special centers have been established across the province to
deal with complaints from overseas investors, the vice governor
said.  
</P>
