<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expansion of Airport in Scenic Huangshan Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Work on expansion of the Huangshan
Airport in the Huangshan Mountain, one of China's major tourist
attractions, started recently.
</P>
<P>
The expansion, scheduled to complete in two years, is expected
to cost some 200 million yuan (about 24 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the airport will be able to accommodate medium-
and large-sized airliners such as Airbus 320s and Boeing 757s. Its
annual handling capacity will be raised to 1.25 million passengers
from 384,000 passengers in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Airport sources said the expansion is designed to meet the
demand of an increasing number of domestic and overseas tourists
to the mountain in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, known for its picturesque pine trees and rocks,
was put on the World Heritage list by the United Nations
Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Nearly five million tourists visited the mountain last year,
including 220,000 from abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
