reporters, "If it turns out that it is not happening, I will
announce what has to be announced."
</P>
<P>
Ha'aretz:
</P>
<P>
-- As of Foreign Minister David Levy's ultimatum, Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak reiterated Tuesday that he has sent emissaries
to Likud Chairman Ariel Sharon in the past few days to examine
whether the Likud party is ready to join the government.
</P>
<P>
Sharon continued Tuesday to deny vehemently that any messengers
had been sent to him by the prime minister, practically charging
the prime minister with lying.
</P>
<P>
"The door to the Likud is open," Barak said in a television
interview. "Let everyone decide which of the two of us he believes
and that will spare me the necessity of embarrassing Sharon."
</P>
<P>
Ma'ariv:
</P>
<P>
-- An Israeli Air Force F-16 warplane crashed Tuesday in the
Negev. The pilot ejected from the aircraft and parachuted to
safety. It was the third F-16 crash this year in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place Tuesday afternoon, about half an hour
after the pilot, a lieutenant doing his compulsory service, took
off from Mt. Ramon base in the Negev on a routine training flight.
</P>
<P>
Following standard procedure, Air Force Commander Dan Halutz
appointed a commission of inquiry to investigate the incident.
Until initial results are received, the Air Force has grounded all
the F-16s of the model that crashed.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot:
</P>
<P>
-- Moshe Katsav, who was sworn in as Israel's eighth president
Tuesday, pledged to avoid getting involved in politics during his
seven-year term, and warned of the turbulence in society expected
to accompany decisions in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Social harmony comes before any peace process," Katsav said
during the Knesset (Parliament) ceremony, adding he is very worried
about the growing gaps between the rich and the poor.
</P>
<P>
"I have promised to mute myself for seven years on political
issues, and I will keep that promise," Katsav later told Israel's
Channel One television, in his first interview as president. "
However, when it comes to social issues, I will not be silent. I
will take up the cause of bridging the gaps in this society even if
it means speaking out." 
</P>
</TEXT>
