<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Rising in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher for the
second straight day in Tokyo Wednesday on continued bargain-
hunting following their previous sharp declines.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 106.52 points, or 0.66
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 16,206.19.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, added 2.76 points or 0.19 percent to 1,482.
60.
</P>
<P>
Trading was thin as investors stayed on the sidelines to
forecast the direction of the market, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 526.65 million
shares from Tuesday's 604.85 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were higher in various business sectors, including
the oil, nonferrous metal, warehousing, transportation machinery
and banking industries.
</P>
<P>
Information and technology issues were mixed following
Tuesday's downturn in New York's Nasdaq composite index.
</P>
<P>
Losers included the rubber, land transportation and wholesale
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 719 to 558 despite the rises in the Nikkei and TOPIX, with
124 issues closing unchanged. 
