<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Cape Verde Parliament Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE (Hebei), August 2 (Xinhua)-- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC),
met with President Antonio Do Espirito Santo Fonseca of Cape Verde
's National People's Assembly (NPA) here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Chinese Government has always attached great
importance to relations with Cape Verde. China highly appreciates
the pursuit of the One-China Policy by the Cape Verde government,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic ties, relations between
China and Cape Verde have been advancing steadily, Li said, adding
China is willing to further develop cooperation in all fields on
the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Inter-parliamentary contacts constitute an important part of
the overall bilateral ties, and the Chinese NPC is willing to
increase communication with the Cape Verde's NPA, Li said, voicing
the conviction that Fonseca's current visit would help promote the
development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Fonseca said although Cape Verde and China are far apart
geographically, the two countries and their peoples have
maintained profound friendship. He expressed gratitude and
appreciation for China's long-term assistance to Cape Verde and
other African countries.
</P>
<P>
The Government of Cape Verde highly emphasizes its relations
with China, and is willing to develop bilateral cooperation in all
fields, he said, stressing Cape Verde firmly supports China's
reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Fonseca and his party arrived in Beijing Tuesday for a 5-day
official goodwill visit as Li's guest. 
</P>
