<HEADLINE> Shanghai Leads China in Patent Application </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's industrial and
financial center, had received 1,617 patent applications on
invention in the first five months this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the State Intellectual Property Office (SIPO)
show that Shanghai led all the other municipalities, provinces, or
autonomous regions in invention patent application in the five-
month period, Wenhui Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Beijing and Guangdong, with about 1,200 and 605 patent
applications respectively, were ranked the second and third, the
Shanghai-based newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The total patent applications in China exceeded one million so
far this year. SIPO encourages localities to apply for more
patents, especially on inventions. 
</P>
