<HEADLINE> China To Build Largest Flour Mill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- China will build its largest flour
mill in Yangpu in the island province of Hainan, the country's
largest special economic zone, an official source said.
</P>
<P>
At the approval of the State Council, the State Development and
Planning Commission has recently endorsed the feasibility study
report on build the mill, which involves a total investment of 860
million yuan (104 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The mill is designed to have an annual processing capacity of
500,000 tons of imported wheat, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory work is underway and the construction is
expected to start before the end of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
