<HEADLINE> Sight First Program Benefits Cataract Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Sight First China Action, a
medical aid program jointly sponsored by China's Ministry of
Health, the China Disabled Persons' Federation, and Lions Clubs
International, has helped more than 10,000 blind people in Nanjing,
capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, regain their sight in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Most of the patients were afflicted with cataract.
</P>
<P>
The program, initiated in 1997 to help cataract sufferers in
rural China, is aimed at curing 105,000 cataract patients in rural
Jiangsu within five years.
</P>
<P>
Cataract-related blindness has afflicted millions of Chinese,
and 400,000 more become new cataract patients every year.
</P>
