<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Internet Surfers in Shenzhen Earn Most: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Internet surfers in the southern
coastal city of Shenzhen earn the most among their Chinese peers,
according to a recent online survey on income.
</P>
<P>
The average after-tax income of the Shenzhen residents is 52,
494 yuan a year, which is followed by the cities of Shanghai,
Zhuhai, Beijing and Guangzhou, whose Internet surfers earn more
than 40,000 yuan, according to today's Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted by ChinaHR.com, a website in Beijing.
Nearly 47,000 respondents from more than 40 Chinese cities and
regions provided their income information.
</P>
<P>
It found that computer-related jobs provided the most
attractive salaries, about 44,102 yuan per year. Lawyers and
accountants were also well-paid, with a yearly average income of
42,995 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Secretaries and administrative assistants earn much less, with
about 26,017 yuan per year; while project managers usually make 53,
573 yuan a year, a group with the highest income.
</P>
<P>
Only about 1.4 percent of the respondents said they were highly
satisfied with their income, and 52.9 per cent said they were not
satisfied.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
