<HEADLINE> Tumor Removed from Newborn's Skull </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Doctors in Shanghai have
successfully removed a 640-cubic-centimeter tumor from the skull
of a four-day-old baby.
</P>
<P>
This is believed to be China's first such operation on a baby
weighing only 3 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The baby, surnamed Zhang, was found to have intracranial
cavernous hemangioma before birth.
</P>
<P>
Further examinations indicated the tumor would soon press the
baby's nerve system, threatening the development of the brain.
</P>
<P>
After careful preparations, doctors at Shanghai's Xinhua
Hospital gingerly did the operation, spending five hours removing
the tumor on July 20.
</P>
<P>
The little patient has been discharged from the hospital after
recovery from the surgery.  
</P>
