<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illustrated Book on Plagues in China Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- An illustrated book on the
history of plagues in China and the latest research achievements
on the infectious disease has been published, the first of its
kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The book, titled "Illustrated Book on Plagues and the
Environment in the People's Republic of China", features the
making, development and distribution of sources of the disease and
ways to prevent and control the epidemic, using 284 maps and
graphics.
</P>
<P>
According to the book, the source of plagues usually contain
high levels of calcium and iron, a discovery which they say will
help prevent and control the epidemic globally.
</P>
<P>
It says the calcium and iron-rich areas are semi-arid desert
grassland in tropical areas and temperate zones, semi-wet
grassland (including those in high and cold areas), and some wet
and hot coastal forests.
</P>
<P>
Tan Jian'an, a research fellow with the Geographic Science and
Resources Institute under the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS)
and one of the editors of the book, said their evidence was based
on the analysis of plagues that hit China in the past two
centuries and related research achievements by medical experts and
geographers from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The book was compiled by the institute in cooperation with the
Ministry of Health and the CAS Environmental Science and
Technology Bureau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
