<HEADLINE> Sampras Survives While Agassi Loses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras won his first match
on Tuesday since winning Wimbledon for the seventh time by beating
Michael Llodra of France 5-7, 6-2, 7-6 (7-4) in the first round of
the $2.95 million Tennis Masters Series-Canada, while top seed
Andre Agassi was knocked out with a 7-6 (7-4), 7-6 (8-6) loss to
Frenchman Jerome Golmard.
</P>
<P>
Playing for the first time since injuring his back in a car
accident, Agassi committed nine double-faults in the loss to
Golmard, who is ranked 61st on the ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
After the match, Agassi complained about his back injury,
saying he had not fully recovered from the injury.
</P>
<P>
He continued that he hoped to be game fit when the U.S. Open
started.
</P>
<P>
Due to his back injury, Agassi was already forced to miss the
United States' semifinal loss to Spain in the Davis Cup and last
week's Los Angeles Open .
</P>
<P>
In contrast to Agassi's loss, second-seeded Sampras survived
early shock of yielding the first set to 20-year-old Llodra, and
controlled the second and third sets.
</P>
<P>
This is their second encounter, with the first also won by
Sampras at the Queen's tournament in mid-June, a Wimbledon warm-up.
</P>
</TEXT>
