<HEADLINE> Presented Oliveira as New Coach of Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lisbon, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Antonio Oliveira was officially
presented as the new coach of Portugal's national football team on
Tuesday and is expected to hold the post through 2004.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made during a ceremony at the Portuguese
Football Federation (FPF) headquarters in Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
Oliveira previously coached the national team from 1994 to 1996,
taking the team to the quarterfinals of the 1996 European
Championship. In 1996-97 and 1997-98 he coached northern club FC
Porto to back-to-back first-place season finishes in the
Portuguese First Division.
</P>
<P>
He replaces Humberto Coelho, who stepped down as national team
head coach after the recent 2000 European Championship, in which
Portugal lost to France 2-1 in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The immediate task at hand is to qualify Portugal for the 2002
World Cup, to be played in Japan and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Portugal will host the European Championship in 2004. 
</P>
</TEXT>
