<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Rice Export Falls by Over Half in Fiscal 1999-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the 1999-2000 year, Myanmar produced 19.92 million tons of
paddy out of 6.25 million hectares cultivated.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Myanmar's rice export was at a trend of down-
sliding. To meet the daily increasing food demand, the country has
since January 1999 leased out 400,000 hectares of vacant and
virgin lands for cultivation to private entrepreneurs, and
introduced policies including those exempting the import duties on
agricultural implements.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar's cultivated land
covers 18.22 million hectares, of which 9.31 million hectares have
been utilized and 8.91 million remain to be reclaimed.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's agriculture accounts for 37 percent of the gross
domestic product and 25 percent of the export value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
