<HEADLINE> China, Thailand to Strengthen Tourism Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- China and Thailand have reached
an agreement on strengthening cooperation in the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that 800,000 Chinese visited Thailand in 1999, and
China has become Thailand's third-largest tourist source.
Meanwhile, more than 100,000 Thai people visited China last year.
</P>
<P>
However, some visitors have complained about price and service
problems.
</P>
<P>
A delegation from Yunnan provincial tourism bureau has visited
Thailand recently, discussing ways to solve the problems. Yunnan
is a southwest China province adjacent to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Sources also say that China, Thailand, Malaysia and Singapore
will hold a meeting this month on improving the tourism
environment. 
