<DOCNO> XIE20000802.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Government Supports Traditional Family </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Australian Associated Press, Prime Minister
John Howard said Wednesday that there was overwhelming support in
his cabinet for the decision to ban single women and gay couples
from in vitro fertilization (IVF) treatment.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the Australian Federal Court made a decision that
a ban on single women wanting to use a Victorian IVF program was
in breach of the Sex Discrimination Act. The cabinet discussed the
issue on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government wants to move an amendment to the act to ensure
that states such as Victoria and Western Australia can continue
their legislation which bans single women and gay couples from
using IVF technology.
</P>
<P>
Howard said Tuesday that children have the right to have a
father and a mother.
</P>
<P>
Traditional family in Australia is in trouble. The young
generation see family as a burden. Meanwhile there are around one
million gays and lesbians in the country who believe they have the
right to have children. The existing welfare system encourages the
life style as single parents enjoy more social aid.
</P>
<P>
Howard's plan is to touch a stormy debate. Both the Labor Party
and Democrats have stated they will vote the amendment down in the
Senate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
