<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Crush AC Milan 5-1 in a Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 1 (Xinhua) -- European champions Real Madrid,
sending an under-strength side, crushed AC Milan 5-1 in a friendly
match at the San Siro on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Milan went into the match with a near full-strength line-up
while Real Madrid didn't field world record signing Luis Figo and
several other top players who featured at Euro 2000.
</P>
<P>
Guti scored an opener in the closing moments of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Seven minutes after the break Fernando Morientes extended their
lead after a neat interchange with Guti.
</P>
<P>
Guti, robbed Milan defender Fabian Ayala and slotted home the
third in the 62nd minute before Cameroon midfielder Samuel Eto'o
made it four with a close range finish.
</P>
<P>
Andriy Shevchenko, top scorer in Serie A last season, pulled
one back for Milan with an 80th minute penalty but Alberto Rivera
wrapped up the victory with a right foot drive eight minutes from
time.
</P>
<P>
Redondo, who signed for Milan from Real last week, watched the
game from the stands.
</P>
<P>
The result was a blow to the Italian club's confidence ahead of
their Champions League qualifying game against Croatia's Dinamo
Zagreb next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
