<HEADLINE> Chinese Talent Discuss Development of Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Thirty doctors from seven Chinese
prestigious universities including Beijing and Qinghua
universities have been making study tours in Tibet since the
beginning of July to explore ways for the development of this
southwest China autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Tibet, they held discussions with local
government officials and representatives from enterprises on
topics involving scientific and technological development and
education, and held training courses for local industrial and
mineral enterprises, government organs and schools.
</P>
<P>
Many of them expressed the intention to work in Tibet, where
they said that they can make full use of local rich natural,
tourism and cultural resources in their research work.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University signed a contract with the regional
government on the development of science and technology,
technological consultation and service, as well as personnel
training.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing Teachers' University, Tibet University and Lhasa
Teachers' University have agreed to conduct a long-term
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China has in the past weeks sent 2,000 doctors to make study
tours in Xinjiang, Tibet and other areas in the country's vast
western region.  
</P>
