<HEADLINE> Artificial Earth Made of Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After twenty years of research, Lin Jingchao from Taiwan, who
has set up a experiment base in Daxing County in south Beijing,
now could make earth from agriculture, petrochemical fibre and
textile wastes.
</P>
<P>
The artificial earth weights only one fifth of the natural
earth at the same volume and is more suitable to growing plants
after sterilization.
</P>
<P>
"My goal is to take the lead in the world to turn all the
building tops green with the artificial earth", said Lin. Now he
has built a garden on the top of his company mansion.  
</P>
