<HEADLINE> No Casinos in Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- No casinos will be allowed to be
set up in western China despite the country's hope for more
foreign investment into the underdeveloped regions, China Daily
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"The central government will absolutely not allow the
establishment of such amusement facilities as casinos, although it
is wooing more foreign investment into the western provinces,"
said an official from the Office for Western Development under the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
The idea to open casinos in the western regions goes against
the aspirations of most Chinese people. "We can't depend on such
ideas to develop the west," the official said.
</P>
<P>
There have been wide reports that local officials in the west
are pushing for greater authority and autonomy by encouraging a
flow of direct overseas investment into the area.
</P>
<P>
Proposals to build China's Las Vegas has also been put forward
as a major effort to promote the flow of foreign funds into the
region, sources claim.  
</P>
