<HEADLINE> Authorities to Deal with Insanitary Restaurants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese authorities, annoyed
by consumers' complaints on the poor sanitary status of many local
restaurants and refreshment rooms, plan to launch a nationwide
inspection on these places.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health and the State Administration of
Internal Trade are ordering all localities to seriously follow the
"Methods on Control over the Sanitation of Food in the Catering
Sector" which came to force on June 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The two departments will try to further increase the awareness
about sanitation among consumers and owners of these eating houses
through publicity activities in various forms.
</P>
<P>
During the overall inspection, the authorities will check up
sanitary conditions in these eating houses and crack down on
unlicensed operations.
</P>
<P>
Local government departments concerned are urged to help local
restaurants and refreshment rooms enhance their technological and
sanitary level.  
</P>
