<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- President of Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
Yasser Arafat arrived in Alexandria, Egypt on Wednesday to consult
with President Hosni Mubarak on ways of pushing forward the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat went into a meeting with Mubarak in the Mediterranean
port city, 220 kilometers northwest of Cairo, upon arrival from the
Sudanese capital of Khartoum during his ongoing tour of Arab
nations. (Egypt-Palestine-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy resigned on
Wednesday from the government led by Prime Minister Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement at his office inside the Knesset
(parliament), Levy said he has submitted his resignation letter to
Barak Wednesday morning, in which he detailed his reasons for
resignation.
</P>
<P>
Under certain government regulations, Levy's resignation will
come into effect within 48 hours after submitting the letter of
resignation. (Israel-FM-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- In the preliminary reading, Israel's Knesset, or
Parliament, Wednesday morning passed a bill calling for dissolving
the Knesset and holding a new election , dealing another blow to
Prime Minister Ehud Barak and his peace efforts.
</P>
<P>
A total of 61 Knesset members voted for the bill, submitted by
the major opposition Likud legislators Silvan Shalom and Limor
Livnat, while 51 voted against it and six legislators abstained,
Israeli television reported. (Israel-Early Elections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KHARTOUM -- The Sudanese government has hailed the decision by
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to restore the country's
membership in the organization as a big step that will promote the
government's efforts to normalize its ties with world financing
institutions and to attract more foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
The El-Alwan newspaper Wednesday quoted Foreign Minister Mustafa
Othman Ismail as saying that the resumption of Sudan's IMF
membership reflects the government's seriousness in implementing
its economic policies. (Sudan-IMF-Membership)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey signed here Wednesday a protocol with Iran to
buy natural gas from Iran, Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the protocol, Turkey will start purchasing 3
billion cubic metres of gas annually from Iran as of July 30, 2001
through a pipeline linking Iran's northwestern Tabriz with Ankara,
which is still under construction. (Turkey-Iran-Natural Gas)
</P>
