<HEADLINE> Brazil Exports to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian exports will grow 17.5
percent this year, according to data supplied Wednesday by the
Development, Industry and Foreign Trade Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Exports will be boosted mainly by the products of the
transports and electronic appliances sectors.
</P>
<P>
Sales forecasts for those two areas will amount to 9.2 billion
dollars and 2.6 billion dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian exports expanded 15.3 percent during the first half
of the year because of the sales of manufactured goods, which grew
22.2 percent over those of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Development, Industry, and Foreign Trade Ministry has
maintained the estimated value of the balance of trade surplus of
the country at the end of the year at 2.8 billion dollars, with
foreseen exports for 56.4 billion dollars.  
