<HEADLINE> Berlin Assumes Leading Role In Germany's Media Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Berlin, the new seat of the
German federal government, has also emerged as the country's media
capital, it was reported here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A study prepared by the Bremen-based BAW Institute for
Economic Research showed Berlin is leading other media centers of
the country in terms of employees' size in the media industry.
</P>
<P>
Berlin had 51,200 people working in the media industry in 1998,
just ahead of Hamburg, which had 51,100 employees in the media
sector, while in Munich, Cologne and Frankfurt, the number varied
from 49,800 to 28,000.
</P>
<P>
The study also showed that information technology plays an
ever important role in the media industry as it will generate an
additional 350,000 jobs for the sector by 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
