<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Industry Continues Recovery in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Greek industry continued its
recovery in 1999, with a big increase in production, sales and
profitability, according to a study conducted by Greece's market
research company ICAP Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The study, which was based on a sample of 4,561 industrial
firms over the past two years, showed a 10 percent increase from
1998, and a favorable factor accounting for the improvement in
results was a larger gross profit margin, which increased to 23.6
percent in 1999 from 23.3 percent in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Of the companies included in the sample, 3,482 were profitable,
compared to 3,437 in 1998, while those businesses which recorded
losses were fewer in number, reducing to 1,079 from 1,124 in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
