<HEADLINE> Nigeria Plans Free Daily Egg for Pupils </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Ministry of Agriculture
has proposed an "egg-in-mid-day meal" scheme for the country's
school kids.
</P>
<P>
The scheme is aimed at supplying free of charge at least one
egg to every primary school pupils per day to ensure the basic
nutrition they get, the Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper,
reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has included the expenses on the scheme in its
next year's budget proposals, pending approval by President
Olusegun Obasanjo.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the agricultural and education ministry said
Wednesday that this was part of the efforts to encourage school
attendance under the recently launched Universal Basic Education (
UBE) program.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), in its bid to
support the UBE, will also provide free daily food to pupils in
four states of the federation to encourage them to attend classes.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a source from the Ministry of Agriculture as
saying that "since the project worked in India, there is no reason
why it should not work in Nigeria, especially as the government is
bent on actualizing the goals of the UBE program." 
</P>
