<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed In Second Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The blue chip stocks on Wall
Street rose again Wednesday as the new economic data eased
uncertainty about higher interest rates. But the tech shares fell.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 80.58 at 10,687.53,
extending its gains of 84.97 points Tuesday and 10.81 points
Monday.
</P>
<P>
But the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 27.06 at 3,
658.46. The composite lost 81.47 points Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 0.60 at 1,438.70.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip stocks rose as the Conference Board said in a
survey that its Composite Index of leading Economic indicators was
unchanged in June, indicating that the U.S. economy is slowing
after six rate hikes in the past 13 months. In addition, the
government reported that U.S. home sales fell in June to their
lowest level in two and a half years.
</P>
<P>
The new data raised hope that the Federal Reserve will leave
rates unchanged at the August 22 meeting. Later last week, a
stronger-than-expected economic growth of 5.2 percent at an annual
rate in the second quarter sparked fears of more rate hikes and
therefore hit the stock market.
</P>
<P>
Among the rate-sensitive stocks which moved up in the financial
sector today were Lehman Brothers and Merrill Lynch. IBM and
Hewlett Packard, both are the Dow's components, were also higher.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq index fell as Wall Street analysts said earnings
forecasts for a number of big tech names will be unsustainable in
the second half of the year. Dell Computer and Cisco System fell
on fears of future profits.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 2.35 at 650.31 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 0.82 at 912.74. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 2.45 at 500.22.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,594 up, 1,295 down and 473
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 983.05 million shares from 917.29
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
