<P>
Other issues such as merchant shipping, technical aid corps,
defense cooperation and visa abolition were also addressed.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed during the recent meeting of the two
country's Joint Commission held in Malabo, capital of Equatorial
Guinea.
</P>
<P>
Onyia, who led the Nigerian delegation to Equatorial Guinea,
said in a statement that developing countries have no option "but
to collaborate, to develop their economic strength and stave off
the harsh realities of the international economic environment."
</P>
